info.name: Pioneer DDJ-WeGO
info.author: Samuel Nicholas
info.description:
built and tested with mixxx 2.0.0 (build 1.12 r5772) My goal with the mapping is to be as close to the behaviour of Pioneers original intention with the device demoed in their marketing material.
Compromises: * auto loop buttons default to creating a loop of 32, mixxx 2.1 will resolve this. * FX[123] are not linked to mixxx controls and are left alone for the user assign. * ctrlB controls the QuickEffectsRack1_[Channeln]_Effect1]
What works: * deck switching for 4 decks * cue, play hotcue[1-4], volume, [low|med|high]eq knobs, headphone cue, browse, load, autoloop, tempo, sampler[1-4], sync_master * scratching * lighting effects for ctrlA, ctrlB and fx buttons, with script option to turn them off. * ctrlA controls pitch, ctrlB controls QuickEffectsRack1
Pioneer marketing text: The DDJ-WeGO is an ultra-compact DJ Controller that enables consumers and music enthusiasts alike to mix their own music creatively. Through various visual and audio cues, the DDJ-WeGO DJ controller makes it easy for beginners to learn how to mix with built-in effects and features:
Jog FX – Allows users to combine multiple effects and control them simultaneously using the Jog wheel. Pulse Control – Provides users with visual prompts with a variety of colored lights on the Jog platters: Mix Pulse – The mix pulse mode shows the difference in pitch of songs currently playing through the light of the Jog wheel. As the pitch of songs begin to match, the intensity of the light increases, allowing the user to visually check that the beats are in sync. In conjunction with the music, the pulse of lights helps to improve beat matching skills. Launch Pulse – Triggers a red light on the Jog wheel to signify that music has been loaded successfully. FX Pulse – The effect being applied to the currently playing song will not only be heard, but will also be represented visually via the light movements on the Jog wheel. USB Powered – The DDJ-WeGO utilizes power from USB connections found on most computers, eliminating the need for an external power supply. Other features o Built-in audio ports for high quality sound input and output. o Built-in sound card for expanded music storage and portability. o Compact size and weighs less than four pounds for easy transportation.
For more information, tips and tricks videos, and Pioneer DJ forums visit www.pioneerdjusa.com https://www.pioneerelectronics.com/PUSA/DJ/Controllers/DDJ-WeGO#overview
